text=http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/city_savannah.png%0a!Character Creation Guide%0a%0aThis guide has been created to lead you through creating a character for the World of Darkness Chronicle: Savannah, GA.  This guide applies to all characters, however, there are venue specific creation rules identified at the end. Lesser Templates (Fae-touched, Sleepwalkers, Ghouls, Wolfblood) creation rules are addressed under their parent venues.%0a%0a!!Approved Books%0a(see [[GameRef.BookPolicy|Book Policies]])%0a%0a[[#restricted]]%0a!!Restricted Slots%0a'''A character may have up to 3 restricted slots between the general and venue specific creation guides.''' Some character aspects may cost more than one restricted slot. Restricted slot costs are identified in red parenthesis:%0a%0a''Example:'' Status 3 %25red%25'''(1)'''%25%25%0a[[#restrictedend]]%0a%0a!!Vitals and Information%0a!!!Age%0aCharacter's actual age and apparent age must be at least 18+.%0a%0a[[#concepts]]%0a!!!Concepts%0a!!!!Emergency Services%0a* '''Police Officer:''' The following will be required:%0a**Attributes: %0a***All attributes must be 2+, minimum Willpower of 5[[%3c%3c]]%0a**Skills: %0a***Mental Skills: Investigation 1, Medicine 1 and either Academics 1 or Politics 1.%0a***Physical Skills: Drive 1, Weaponry 1 and a total of 5 dots between Athletics, Brawl and Firearms with at least 1 dot in each.%0a***Social Skills: Intimidation 1, Persuasion 1 and either Empathy 1 or Subterfuge 1.%0a**Merits: %0a***No merits are required, suggested merits are Resources, Sworn Officer, Police Tactics, and Status (Police).%0a%0a* '''Detective:''' The following will be required:%0a**Attribute: %0a***Intelligence 3, Wits 3, Composure 3 and either Presence or Manipulation 3%0a**Skills: %0a***Mental Skills: Academics 1, Investigation 3,Politics 1%0a***Physical Skills: Same as Police Officer%0a***Social Skills: 5 dots among Empathy,Intimidation, Persuasion and Streetwise%0a**Merits: %0a***No merits are required, suggested merits are Resources, Sworn Officer, Police Tactics, and Status (Police).%0a**Additional Requirements%0a***Homicide: Medicine 1 or Science 2%0a***Robbery: None%0a***Property Crimes: None%0a***Narcotics: Streetwise 3%0a***Special Victims: Medicine 1, Empathy 3, Willpower 6%0a***Information Crimes: either Academics 2 with an Accounting Specialty, Computer 3 or Crafts 2 with an Accounting Specialty%0a***Vice: Socialize 2 and Streetwise 2%0a***Intelligence: Contacts Merit 4%0a***Organized Crime Task Force: Politics 2%0a***Gang Task Force: Streetwise 2%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0aNote: Requirements are in addition to a Police officer, since you would still start your career as a Police Officer%0a%0a* '''Evidence Analysis:''' The following will be required:%0a**Attributes: %0a***Intelligence 3, Wits 3 and Composure 3%0a**Skills: %0a***Mental Skills: Academics 1, Computer 1, Investigation 3 and a total of 3 dots between Medicine and Science%0a**Advantages:%0a***Morality 6, Willpower 5 and no severe derangements%0a%0a* '''SWAT Officer:''' The following will be required:%0a**Attributes: %0a***All Mental 2, all Physical 3 and Composure 2%0a**Skills: %0a***Physical Skills: Athletics 2 and Firearms 3 %0a**Merits: %0a***No merits are required, suggested merits are Resources, Sworn Officer, Police Tactics, and Status (Police).%0a***Advantages: Morality 5, Willpower 5, Initiative 6 and no derangements that affect decision-making or combat capability.%0a%0a!!!!Medical Services%0a* '''Emergency Medical Technician:''' The following will be required:%0a**Attributes: %0a***Intelligence 2 Wits 3 Stamina 3%0a**Skills: %0a***Mental Skills:Academics 1 Computer 1 Medicine 2-3(Depending on Degree of Training)%0a***Physical Skills: Athletics Drive 1%0a***Social Skills: Empathy 1%0a**Merits: %0a***Suggestions Iron Stamina, Status (Medical), Fast Reflexes, Stunt Driver%0a%0a* '''Doctor:''' The following will be required:%0a**Attributes: %0a***Intelligence 3 Wits 3 Stamina 3 Dexterity 3(Surgeons)%0a**Skills: %0a***Mental Skills: Academics 3 Investigation 1 Medicine 3 (Often with a Specialty) Science 2%0a***Social Skills: Empathy 1 Socialize 1%0a**Merits: %0a*** Suggestions are Contacts (Medicine, Business Legal), Encyclopedic Knowledge, Fame, Holistic Awareness, Retainer, Status (Medical)%0a%0a[[#conceptsend]]%0a!!!Equipment%0a* '''Armory Costs:''' As of page 13 of Armory, costs for weapons are 1 dot higher than they should be, so consider them one lower. Be sure to check individual weapon/material sections for cost changes and other effects.%0a* '''Silencers:''' Legal if registered, and can be home-made as per the rules in Armory (sidebar on p167.)%0a* '''Drugs:''' If it's just a few doses there are no pre-requisites, get high IC as you please. For anything more, characters require Status 1+ in Underworld or Medicine (depending on drug type). For being prescribed something unethically, Underworld Allies 2+ or Medical Allies 3+ is needed.%0a* '''Military or Police grade equipment:''' Legal if registered, but keep costs and ease of tracking in mind.%0a* '''Silver or cold iron weapons''' %25red%25'''(1)'''%25%25%0a%0a!!Attributes and Skills%0a* '''Attribute 4+ %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25: Strength 4 costs 1 restricted slot, Strength 5 costs 2 restricted slots%0a* '''Attribute 1''': Require a detailed explanation as to why your character is below the human average in your history.%0a* '''Skill 4+ %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25: Brawl 4 costs 1 restricted slot, Brawl 5 costs 2 restricted slots%0a* '''Occult''': Knowledge of the other supernaturals is governed by your '''[[GameRef.GeneralHouseRules#Occult|Occult]]''' rating. Previous experience with the Supernatural outside of your venue beyond "non-splat" creatures (such as ghosts) is discouraged and requires a detailed and fitting explanation in your history. An existing PC of the other venue (not NPC) may agree to 'sponsor' your knowledge, however this means they have risked the secrecy of their existence. %0a%0a!!Merits%0a* '''Merit 4+ %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25: This includes non-scaled merits such as Striking Looks.%0a**Exception: Wolf-Blooded 4 costs no restricted slots. Wolf-Blooded 5 costs 1 restricted slot.%0a* '''Allies, Contacts, Mentor, Retainer''': Requires an explanation of the nature of your relationship and how it is maintained with the people represented by these merits. Be prepared for the possibility of your ally, contact, mentor or retainer requiring something of you. Otherwise, all benefits associated with these merits per the book are provided as usual.%0a* '''Ambidextrous %25red%25(1)'''%25%25%0a* '''Decorated 3 %25red%25(1)'''%25%25%0a* '''Fame 3 %25red%25(1)'''%25%25: Fame should be relevant to the Savannah, GA.%0a* '''Fighting Style 2+ or second Fighting Style %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25: Boxing 2 costs 1 restricted slot. Boxing 1 and Wrestling 1 costs 1 restricted slot. Boxing 1 and Wrestling 2 costs 2 restricted slots.%0a* '''Gunslinger %25red%25(1)'''%25%25%0a* '''Resources 3+ %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25: Resources 4 costs 2 restricted slots, Resources 5 costs 3 restricted slots.%0a*'''Retainers''':%0a>>lrindent frame bgcolor=#eeeeee padding=15px%3c%3c%0a||border=1%0a||!Merit Level||!Max Die Pool||!Dice to Distribute||!Resistance||!Merits||%0a|| 1 || 2 || 4 || 1 || 0 ||%0a|| 2 || 4 || 8 || 2 || 1 ||%0a|| 3 || 6 || 14 || 2 || 2 ||%0a|| 4 || 8 || 20 || 3 || 3 (max 2), 1* ||%0a|| 5 || 10 || 28 || 3 || 4 (max 3), 2* ||%0a->*Supernatural points%0a%0a:Retainer Merits allowed: %0aGhoul, Sleepwalker(Somnambulist), Danger Sense, Direction Sense, Fleet of Foot, Strong Back, Source Sympathy (ghouls), Unobtrusive (ghouls), Iron Stomach, Multi-Lingual, Natural Immunity, New Identity, Strong Lungs, Sworn Officer, Toxin Resistance, Status, Eidetic memory, Language%0a%0a:Ghouls:%0a*First supernatural physical supernatural dot from their dormitor is free. %0a*Retainer 4 or 5: 1 additional in-clan discipline dot that dormitor can teach.%0a* Die pools must be purchased as normal for disciplines using die pools.%0a%0a:Sleepwalkers:%0a*This overrides the Sleepwalker Merit. (MtA:Core p. 88)%0a*Retainer must be at least 2 dots. Retainer merit dots equate to level of Sleepwalker. (I.e., Retainer 3 = Sleepwalker 3) Capped at 4.%0a*Sleepwalker retainers use the [[GameRef.MtAHouseRules#HR-4|Somnambulist]] merit.%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a* '''Status 3 %25red%25(1)'''%25%25: This is per area such as Status 3 Police. Status 1 in Police, Medical and Media does not cost a restricted slot. Higher status in an area may also have other requirements as pointed out in the books.%0a* '''Striking Looks''': This merit is intended to draw attention to your character, both positive and negative (stalkers, serial killers, etc.) Be prepared for consequences.%0a%0a!!Flaws%0a* A character may have 1 flaw, and will be expected to role play it consistently. XP will be awarded in ST-run scenes if the Flaw is truly an obstacle for you.%0a%0a!!Traits%0a* '''Morality etc. 6- %25red%25(1 per dot)'''%25%25: Morality 6 costs 1 restricted slot. Morality 5 costs 2 restricted slots. Morality can be dropped a maximum of 2 times at Character creation for 5XP each time (maximum 10XP). Each drop requires a derangement check as usual which will take place during sanctioning.%0a%0a!!Banned%0a*Anachronistic or over-the-top concepts will not be sanctioned. Examples: Ninja, serial killer, Queen of England.%0a*Active Federal agents (FBI, CIA, NSA, etc.)%0a*Owning or controlling a large corporation%0a*Signature characters of any book, film or other popular fiction%0a*Supernatural Power Stat at 4+ (Gnosis, Primal Urge, etc.)%0a*Decorated 4+%0a*Characters remade from another site or previous edition of Wanton Wicked.%0a%0a!! Goals and Beliefs%0aGoals and Beliefs are an integral component to characters on Wanton Wicked. They provide an easy reference for the STs for what is driving the character and where they are going to go. Goals and Beliefs are defined during Character Creation, but they are expected to evolve through out the character's story. %0a!!!Goals: What the character is working towards specifically%0aThese can be short term or long term, but they are something your PC is actively seeking to accomplish. Examples: Finish college, start a business, investigate rumors of family treasure.%0a!!!Beliefs: What drives the character%0aBeliefs help to identify what is important to a character, but also what motivates them.  As such, beliefs identified on the character sheet should be ''active''. Example: The world is going to end (passive) vs. the world is going to end unless I do something about it (active). %0a%0aBeliefs can also be "ST Hooks" that encourage a storyteller to run a story line which calls into the foreground or challenges your character's beliefs. Examples: I must never risk my loved ones, magic is more important than anything or anyone else, the safety of my friends and family is more important than my own.%0a%0a!!!!Reasons to Be: Suggestions for developing beliefs%0a*First Belief should tie to a character's past. How have they reacted to changing to a supernatural? How have they reacted to their brush with the supernatural (if mortal)?%0a*Second Belief links the character directly to the situation at hand. Why is he where he is? What does he currently have a stake in?%0a*Third Belief should be used to create hints and intimations of the future of the character - a distant goal, a lost love, ideas, editcs, oaths, etc - stuff that's not immediately tied to the game at hand, but once this part of his life is over, will propel him forward to continue the story.%0a%0a!!Venue Character Creation Guides%0aReview the Creation Guide for your specific venue before completing your character. Unless specifically noted in a venue Creation Guide, all rules in the primary Creation Guide are in effect.  %0a%0aIt may also be useful to visit the Venue's main page to locate the Player Guide. This may  help you with any more extensive clarifications, methods of contacting the storyteller for your venue, and any other considerations.%0a%0a[[#CTL]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_changeling.png (:toggle hide CtLCG:)%0a>>id=CtLCG border='0px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a(:Include GameRef.CtLMaster#Creation#CreationEnd:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a[[#MTA]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_mage.png (:toggle hide MtACG:)%0a>>id=MtACG border='0px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a(:Include GameRef.MtAMaster#Creation#CreationEnd:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a[[#M]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_mortal.png (:toggle hide MCG:)%0a>>id=MCG border='0px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a(:include GameRef.WodMMaster#Creation#CreationEnd:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a[[#VTR]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_vampire.png (:toggle hide VCG:)%0a>>id=VCG border='0px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a(:include GameRef.VtRMaster#CharacterCreation#CharacterCreationEnd:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a[[#WTF]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_werewolf.png (:toggle hide WtFCG:)%0a>>id=WtFCG border='0px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a(:include Players.WtFGuidelines#Creation#CreationEnd:)%0a>>%3c%3c
