diff:1372652124:1372652124:=1,239d0%0a%3c [[#top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:table border=0 style=float width=40%25 align=right cellspacing=0 :)%0a%3c (:cellnr align=center:)%0a%3c (:cellnr:)%0a%3c (:cellnr bgcolor=#365776 align=center:)%0a%3c '''Contents'''%0a%3c (:cellnr:)%0a%3c *[[#Restricted|Restricted]]%0a%3c *[[#GeneralConsiderations|General Considerations]]%0a%3c *[[#Equipment|Equipment]]%0a%3c *[[#Banned|Banned]]%0a%3c *[[#GoalsandBeliefs|Goals and Beliefs]]%0a%3c *[[#IncentiveXP|Incentive XP]]%0a%3c *[[#Venues|Venue Specific Creation Rules]]%0a%3c **[[#WOD|World of Darkness]]%0a%3c **[[#WODS|World of Darkness: Supernaturals]]%0a%3c **[[#VTR|Vampire]]%0a%3c **[[#MTA|Mage]]%0a%3c **[[#WTF|Werewolf]]%0a%3c **[[#WB|Wolf Blood]]%0a%3c **[[#CTL|Changeling]]%0a%3c **[[#HTV|Hunter]]%0a%3c **[[#GTS|Geist]]%0a%3c (:tableend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Restricted]]%0a%3c [+'''Restricted Slots'''+]\\%0a%3c You may have up to three restricted slots.%0a%3c %0a%3c * Any Attribute, Skill, Merit or Power at 4+, costs one restricted slot per dot. Thus a merit, attribute, skill or power at 4 dots costs 1 restricted slot, while a merit, attribute, skill or power at 5 dots costs 2 restricted slots. Please note that some merits have more specific limitations.%0a%3c **If a supernatural bonus dot gives you any of the above traits at 4+, it is not counted as a restricted item.%0a%3c **This applies to non-scaled merits as well.%0a%3c *'''''Exception:''''' Wolf-Blooded 4 costs no restricted slots. Wolf-Blooded 5 costs 1 restricted slot.%0a%3c * Resources 3+. It takes a substantial amount of work or an important turn of events in one's life to have this much ready-money. (Resources 4 would cost a second slot, as a scaled merit at 4. Five would cost a third slot.)%0a%3c * Decorated 3 takes one restricted slot. Decorated 4+ is banned.%0a%3c * Status 3: Status above 2 in a single organization is a Restricted Item. This means you don't have to start as a rookie and can get involved in larger and/or more ongoing events with a greater degree of freedom. There's plenty of room to work up from there, and if you really want to play a beat cop, Status 2 is still there for you unRestricted. Please note that you must also fulfill additional requirements for the status, as pointed out in the WoD book or specialty books such as Asylum or 13th Precinct.  See [[CityBook.TheLaw | The Law]] for more information on playing law enforcement concepts.  Also note that Status 4+ is banned at Character Creation.%0a%3c **Examples:%0a%3c ***Status (Police) 3 - one restricted slot%0a%3c ***Status (Police) 3, Status (Medical) 3 - two restricted slots%0a%3c *Fighting Styles. Each dot after the first in one or more Fighting Styles is one Restricted Item. The first dot of a fighting style should represent an enthusiast who trains weekly, while two dots would be an active hobbyist who trains a few times a week. Note that this is cumulative; Boxing 1 costs no restricted slots, Boxing 1, Wrestling 1 costs one restricted slot, and Boxing 1, Wrestling 2 costs two restricted slots.%0a%3c *Gunslinger%0a%3c *Ambidextrous%0a%3c * The Luxury Merit from Seers of the Throne costs a restricted slot, in addition to any restricted slots for its point rating.%0a%3c * Fame 3. Note that Fame is calculated based on relevance in the setting. Being famous among Uzbekistan farmers does nothing in San Diego%0a%3c * The Dragon's Tongue Merit (both versions) from Inferno costs a restricted slot for character-types other than Possessed.%0a%3c * Each reduction of Morality (thus, dropping Morality from 7 to 6 for 5 XP is 1 restricted slot, dropping from Morality 7 to 5 for 10 XP is 2 restricted slots). Morality can only be dropped twice at character creation, as per the book. Note that some character types (Ghouls, Blood Bathers, for example) may be exceptions to this rule. Also note that each drop in Morality requires a derangement check as usual.%0a%3c * Supernatural Power Stat 3 costs one restricted slot.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#GeneralConsiderations]]%0a%3c [+'''General Considerations'''+]%0a%3c %0a%3c * Striking Looks. Understand that in taking it, you're asking for a tremendous amount of attention, and a lot of it negative. Be beautiful, but be prepared for the consequences (stalkers, serial killers, etc.).%0a%3c * Allies, Contacts, Mentor and Retainer. These merits are people or groups of people that you can call on for some kind of help. Rare is the relationship that goes one way, however. By taking either of these merits, you can, of course, reap the rewards they provide as usual. However, understand that the door is open for your acquaintances and informants to call on you as well. Be prepared to describe what the nature of your relationship is with these people/groups, and how it's maintained. If you can't do this with some ease, reconsider taking the merit.%0a%3c * Flaws. You may take one flaw. You will be expected to roleplay it consistently. XP will be awarded in ST-run scenes if your Flaw truly was an obstacle for you.%0a%3c * Attributes at 1. You will be expected to detail why that attribute is below the human average in your history.%0a%3c * Knowledge of the Supernatural is governed by your [[OccultLore|Occult score]]. Actual experience with the Supernatural beyond "non-splat" creatures (such as ghosts) and your own is heavily discouraged and STs may ask you to remove it from your background if they do not find it fitting (Hunters are, of course, an exception to this). If an existing character of the type in question agrees to "sponsor" your knowledge, mortal characters may also be excempt.%0a%3c       Note: This cannot be an NPC who 'sponsors' you, it must be a PC.%0a%3c * Lesser Templates are considered part of their parent venue.%0a%3c * If using merits from a book belonging to another venue, be prepared to show the sanctioning storyteller the full text of the merit.%0a%3c * [[Retainer Rules]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Equipment]]%0a%3c [+'''Equipment'''+]%0a%3c %0a%3c * Silencers. (Require Criminal Allies or Status 2+)%0a%3c * Most functional archaic weaponry. (Requires a suitable level of Resources and/or, with a good history, Status or Allies)%0a%3c * Drugs. (Require Criminal/Medicine Status 1+, depending on type of drug, or Criminal Allies 2+ or Medical Allies 3+, assuming you're being prescribed something unethically.)%0a%3c * Military or Police grade equipment. Unless you have a background (including a sufficient level of Status or Allies) that would warrant it, automatic weapons, explosives, high-grade ballistic armor and the like are unavailable to you at chargen. No, your daddy didn't smuggle his M-16 home from Vietnam.%0a%3c * Silver or cold iron weapons of any kind.%0a%3c * For more information on San Diego Concealed Carry Weapon Laws click [[http://www.sdsheriff.net/licensing/ccw.html|here]]. and [[http://www.calguns.net/calgunforum/showpost.php?s=d101836005a15198d56f0088a0873558&p=3235518&postcount=19|here]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Banned]]%0a%3c [+'''Banned'''+]%0a%3c %0a%3c * Anachronistic or over-the-top concepts. Concepts like Ninja, Serial Killer, or Batman will not be sanctioned.%0a%3c * Active federal agents (FBI, CIA, NSA, etc.).%0a%3c * Owning or controlling a large corporation.%0a%3c * Signature characters from any of the books or from popular fiction.%0a%3c * PC Prometheans are not allowed in the Wanton Wicked Chronicle.%0a%3c * PC Changing Breeds%0a%3c * Supernatural Power Stat at 4+.%0a%3c * The Decorated Merit at 4+.%0a%3c * Direct remakes of characters from another site or earlier edition of Wanton Wicked. While we have little control over checking if a concept or character sheet is being recycled, we'd prefer that characters have their "serial numbers" filed off if remade for Wanton Wicked.%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#GoalsandBeliefs]]%0a%3c [+'''Goals and Beliefs'''+]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c Goals and Beliefs are an integral component to characters on Wanton Wicked. They provide an easy reference for the STs for what is driving the character and where they are going to go. Goals and Beliefs are defined during Character Creation, but they are expected to evolve through out the character's story.%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c !!!'''Goals'''%0a%3c Goals are what the character is working towards in specific. They can be either short term or long term, but they are a direction for the PC to work towards. PCs should always have goals. If a PC has no goals that they are working towards, then that means that they are doing nothing of note to advance any storylines and will be removed. Games exist to tell stories. Sometimes in a game a character will get to a point where there is nothing further for them to really work towards. Take that as a hint that it is time to retire that character and find something new to play.%0a%3c *'''Sample goals:'''%0a%3c **Finish College%0a%3c **Discovered where my uncle disappeared to three months ago%0a%3c **Create and run my own business%0a%3c **Get rid of the corrupt Lieutenant on the police force%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!'''Beliefs'''%0a%3c Beliefs are what drive your character. What more, they are also something completely player driven. When you make a belief for your character you are stating that you want to see something related to that belief come up in the game, probably to complicate a character's life. Beliefs should NEVER be passive. A belief that says 'The world is going to end' is not a good belief. A belief that says 'The World is going to end, unless I do something about it' is a lot better because it is active. A belief like 'I will not follow the expectations of my family.' is begging for an ST to run a storyline where familial expectations for the character come into play.%0a%3c %0a%3c ->'''Quote from Burning Wheel'''%0a%3c ->Get inside your character's head. Figure out what he's all about. What does he believe in? What does he want? What does he hate? How does he see the world? What does he love? ''Think'' about him. These are all important aspects for a character's Beliefs. In order to get perspective look at the concept and choices you've made for the character, reflect on how those would affect him and make some notes.%0a%3c %0a%3c ->'''Reasons to Be:'''%0a%3c ->One of the best methods I've found for creating Beliefs is as follows:%0a%3c **First Belief should tie to a character's past. How have they reacted to changing to a supernatural? How have they reacted to their brush with the supernatural (if mortal)?%0a%3c **Second Belief links the character directly to the situation at hand. Why is he where he is? What does he currently have a stake in?%0a%3c **Third Belief should be used to create hints and intimations of the future of the character - a distant goal, a lost love, ideas, editcs, oaths, etc - stuff that's not immediately tied to the game at hand, but once this part of his life is over, will propel him forward to continue the story.%0a%3c %0a%3c ->'''Sample Beliefs:'''%0a%3c **I must never risk my loved ones%0a%3c **Magic is more important than anything else%0a%3c **Vampires are lords above the kine%0a%3c **Vampires are worse than humans%0a%3c **I must protect my territory at all costs%0a%3c **I must not let shame come to my family%0a%3c **The safety of my coterie/cabal/pack/friends before my own%0a%3c **Mystical knowledge is meant to be known%0a%3c %0a%3c ->''Note:'' Beliefs do not equal religious convictions.\\%0a%3c ''Note 2:'' Having Beliefs written out like this is an idea I'm yoinking from Burning Wheel a fantastic fantasy RPG system that I highly recommend.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#IncentiveXP]]%0a%3c [+'''Incentive XP'''+]%0a%3c Incentive XP can only be taken at creation. It is given to characters that meet certain benchmarks that the STs are currently encouraging. Up to 5 General iXP may be taken, as well as 5  venue specific iXP. The General XP pool on the sheet may read -10 when you create your character, and all iXP that you are claiming should be listed in the Notes section for review by the sanctioning ST. %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ->'''Age'''%0a%3c ->Apparent Age, for creatures that age oddly%0a%3c **+0xp: 18 - 25%0a%3c **+1xp: 26 - 35%0a%3c **+2xp: 36 - 55%0a%3c **+3xp: 56+%0a%3c %0a%3c ->'''Origin''''^1^'%0a%3c **+4xp: San Diego%0a%3c **+3xp: California%0a%3c **+2xp: USA, Mexico%0a%3c **+1xp: China, Vietnam, Philippines (significant immigrant populations of >= 2%25 of overall population'^2^')%0a%3c %0a%3c [--Note 1: Origin covers place of birth primarily, but the more XP you get, the more limits your character has on where they grew up/were raised/spent most of their life. A person born in San Diego needs to have spent the majority of their life in San Diego, or get bumped down to the next appropriate level, whereas the characters who take up a lesser slot can move closer to San Diego at any time after their birth without receiving a penalty.--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [--[[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/ADPTable?_bm=y&-geo_id=16000US0666000&-qr_name=ACS_2008_3YR_G00_DP3YR5&-ds_name=ACS_2008_3YR_G00_&-_lang=en&-redoLog=false&-_sse=on|Note 2]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Venues]]%0a%3c [++'''Venue Specific Character Creation Rules'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Individual venues may place additional addendum to the Code of Conduct for their players, pages also include instructions for the preferred method of contacting storytellers on the team, how to schedule a scene, and how to join the venue. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#WOD]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#365776%25World of Darkness%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box1 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box1 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.WoDCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#WODS]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#8450b5%25World of Darkness: Supernaturals%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box10 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box10 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.WoDSCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#VTR]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#A00000%25Vampire%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box2 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box2 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.VampireCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#MTA]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#1b9ad0%25Mage%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box3 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box3 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.MageCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#WTF]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#996600%25Werewolf%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box4 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box4 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.WerewolfCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#WB]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#996600%25Wolfblood%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box9 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box9 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.Wolf-BloodedCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#CTL]]%0a%3c '''%25green%25Changeling%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box5 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box5 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.ChangelingCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#HTV]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#305d52%25Hunter%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box6 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box6 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a%3c (:include GameRef.HunterCharacterCreation:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#GTS]]%0a%3c '''%25color=#70b0ca%25Geist%25%25'''%0a%3c (:toggle id=box7 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box7 bord